You can use coordinated shutdown (https://doc.akka.io/docs/akka/current/coordinated-shutdown.html) for this.

You can terminate the system in a `PreDestroy` callback like:

    CoordinatedShutdown.get(system)
                       .runAll(CoordinatedShutdown.jvmExitReason())
                       .get(60, TimeUnit.SECONDS);

And then you can register your actor as follows:

    CoordinatedShutdown.get(system())
                        .addCancellableTask(
                                CoordinatedShutdown.PhaseServiceRequestsDone(),
                                &quot;shutdown-actor&quot;,
                                () -&gt; {
                                    return Patterns.ask(self, new Stop(), Duration.ofSeconds(60))
                                                        .thenApply(msg -&gt; Done.getInstance());
                            });

This will postpone the shutdown of the system until a response to Stop has been received

